A close-up studio product visualization cross-section cutaway of a modular flight helmet shell matrix. The outer 1.2mm active camouflage skin is composed of a flexible translucent hydrogel grid holding micro-etched channels of shifting green and turquoise guanine nanocrystals. The middle structural shell shows a dense, matte-black 8.0mm aerospace-grade carbon fiber polycarbonate weave with visible continuous graphene interleave lines. The innermost layer is a removable 14.0mm forest-green variable-density flexible elastomer liner showing woodpecker sponge voids and horizontal 2.4mm thermal venting paths, bright overhead studio lights, photorealistic metal and resin textures, 8k --ar 16:9
